  "text": "There are mainly two types of DC motor used in the industry. The first one is the conventional DC motor where the flux is produced by the current through the field coil of the stationary pole structure. The second type is the brushless DC motor (BLDC motor) where the permanent magnet provides the necessary air gap flux instead of the wire-wound field poles [CITATION_1] .",
